01:21.765 --> 01:23.232
[Cash register bell dings]

01:23.233 --> 01:26.566
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ooh
ooh ooh ♪

01:28.233 --> 01:33.566
<font color="#ff8c00">Sync & corrections by Alice</font>
<font color="#ff8c00">www.addic7ed.com</font>

01:38.950 --> 01:40.752
Ho ho ho!

01:40.753 --> 01:43.254
Talking to you, Max.

01:43.255 --> 01:45.056
I know.
What's up, Andy?

01:45.057 --> 01:47.591
I brought some Christmas candy
from my shop for the diner.

01:47.592 --> 01:49.660
Oh.

01:52.464 --> 01:54.966
Look, Max,
Santa did come.

01:54.967 --> 01:57.735
From just a kiss?

01:57.736 --> 02:00.738
Well, you didn't see what
she was doing with her hands.

02:01.239 --> 02:02.306
I taught her that.

02:02.307 --> 02:05.076
That's my gift to you.
Merry Christmas.

02:06.577 --> 02:08.910
Hey, is everything okay
with your shop?

02:09.314 --> 02:11.082
'Cause the landlord
came into my store today

02:11.083 --> 02:12.516
and mentioned you guys
hadn't paid your rent.

02:12.517 --> 02:14.552
If there's a problem,
I'd be more than happy to help.

02:14.553 --> 02:15.786
Well, the fact is,
we just don't have--

02:15.787 --> 02:18.122
Don't have a clue
why our online payments

02:18.123 --> 02:20.858
just never go through.
Technology, right?

02:20.859 --> 02:22.760
You used to be able
to shake the mailman's hand.

02:22.761 --> 02:25.396
Now it's all holograms
and lasers.

02:25.397 --> 02:28.466
Grandma's right,
those were the days.

02:28.467 --> 02:30.768
It was a more honest time.

02:31.269 --> 02:34.102
Okay. Well, I gotta go.
A kiss for Caroline.

02:36.608 --> 02:39.043
Oh, that was a new kind
of kiss.

02:39.044 --> 02:40.478
I liked it.

02:40.479 --> 02:43.581
Max taught me.

02:44.950 --> 02:47.318
What's with the lies?
Just tell him the truth.

02:47.319 --> 02:48.853
We can't pay our rent,
life sucks,

02:48.854 --> 02:51.689
and you need wine
before oral.

02:52.490 --> 02:53.391
No need.

02:53.392 --> 02:55.159
We still have
two other private parties

02:55.160 --> 02:57.028
set up for this month:
The <i>Quinceanera</i>

02:57.029 --> 03:00.231
for that pregnant girl,
and then her baby shower.

03:00.232 --> 03:02.066
Plus, the holidays
are coming,

03:02.067 --> 03:04.168
so we should
get our decorations up asap,

03:04.169 --> 03:05.803
or Santa won't know
where to find us.

03:05.804 --> 03:07.338
Oh, he'll know
where to find us.

03:07.339 --> 03:08.506
We'll be
the two evicted girls

03:08.507 --> 03:10.808
eating fruitcake
out of a Dumpster.

03:11.009 --> 03:14.142
Oh, look, here comes
one of the reindeers now.

03:15.814 --> 03:19.147
You look like
a Korean coat rack.

03:20.851 --> 03:22.684
Everybody can stop looking.

03:22.888 --> 03:24.290
We found the Grinch.

03:25.591 --> 03:29.093
No wonder it's so angry,
it's working for minimum wage.

03:32.798 --> 03:35.399
Oh, you're hanging
the Christmas decorations.

03:35.400 --> 03:37.034
I already put up
the mistletoe.

03:37.035 --> 03:38.302
Where?

03:39.303 --> 03:41.636
Let's just say
it's very well-hung.

03:45.811 --> 03:47.578
Well,
all my checks are in,

03:47.579 --> 03:50.314
so I have to run
and make a cupcake delivery.

03:50.315 --> 03:51.949
Here, take this
and put it in the till.

03:51.950 --> 03:53.417
I did a cupcake run
last night too.

03:53.418 --> 03:56.153
- Wait, who orders cupcakes
at 2:00 a.m.?

03:56.154 --> 03:58.089
Um, my friends.

03:58.090 --> 03:59.423
You don't have
any friends.

03:59.424 --> 04:01.659
I have
so many friends.

04:01.660 --> 04:02.827
Who are your friends?

04:02.828 --> 04:04.361
Some people I know.

04:04.362 --> 04:05.763
Then how come
I've never met them?

04:05.764 --> 04:07.932
Well, they don't like you.

04:07.933 --> 04:09.366
But they don't know me.

04:09.367 --> 04:11.836
They don't like
what they've heard about you.

04:11.837 --> 04:14.205
But who would they have
heard things from but you?

04:14.206 --> 04:16.373
Maybe from
my other group of friends.

04:16.374 --> 04:18.442
They don't like you either.
Later.

04:22.847 --> 04:24.248
Max,
you can turn around.

04:24.249 --> 04:26.684
That's right,
I followed you.

04:29.554 --> 04:31.155
Sorry for following you.

04:31.156 --> 04:33.124
It's just, you have
the hair and jacket of a woman.

04:33.125 --> 04:35.559
In a good way.
[Chuckles]

04:35.560 --> 04:37.528
Did you actually
think that was me?

04:37.529 --> 04:39.563
My beard
is much thicker.

04:39.564 --> 04:40.798
Well, where are we going?

04:40.799 --> 04:42.299
Why are we
in this seedy building

04:42.300 --> 04:43.701
that smells
like marijuana?

04:43.702 --> 04:46.437
Oh, my God, is this
where your mom lives?

04:46.438 --> 04:49.740
You think
my mom lives indoors?

04:49.741 --> 04:51.675
Okay, look,
for the last few nights,

04:51.676 --> 04:53.944
my dealer calls me
after she sells pot to people,

04:53.945 --> 04:56.113
and then I sell those people
the munchies they need.

04:56.114 --> 04:58.449
Max, this is New York.
That's illegal!

04:58.450 --> 05:00.951
No, giant sodas
are illegal.

05:00.952 --> 05:03.287
This is me selling cupcakes
to make our rent.

05:03.288 --> 05:05.222
And besides,
it's not a big deal.

05:05.223 --> 05:07.158
Pot's legal in Washington,
Massachusetts,

05:07.159 --> 05:08.659
Colorado,
and California.

05:08.660 --> 05:10.594
Well, thank you
for the stoner's summary

05:10.595 --> 05:12.296
of the last election,
but we don't live

05:12.297 --> 05:14.165
in any of those places,

05:14.166 --> 05:15.566
and I do not approve of pot
at all.

05:15.567 --> 05:17.268
It makes people
lazy and lethargic,

05:17.269 --> 05:19.303
and drains
all one's ambitions.

05:19.304 --> 05:21.972
God, you're fun.

05:21.973 --> 05:24.074
Look, on the other side
of this door

05:24.075 --> 05:27.077
is money to help us make
the $600 more we need for rent.

05:27.078 --> 05:28.846
It's totally up to you.

05:28.847 --> 05:31.248
Should I knock,
or not knock?

05:31.249 --> 05:32.783
What's good, Max?

05:32.784 --> 05:34.518
Hey, Keefer.
This is my friend Caroline.

05:34.519 --> 05:35.786
Pleasure, my goddess.

05:35.787 --> 05:39.056
Come on in.
I just broke out some dank nugs.

05:39.057 --> 05:42.326
Oh, thanks, but we actually
just had some dank nugs.

05:42.327 --> 05:45.362
First of all,
that's your new nickname,

05:45.363 --> 05:47.198
and, Keefer,
I don't want to rush you,

05:47.199 --> 05:49.800
but me and dank nugs
have to get home.

05:49.801 --> 05:52.436
Okay, cool, I'll be right back
with the cash.

05:52.437 --> 05:55.139
Second-hand smoke,
second-hand smoke.

05:55.140 --> 05:57.408
Second-hand nerd,
second-hand nerd.

05:57.409 --> 06:00.742
Here you go, they were feeling
kinda generous.

06:00.979 --> 06:01.979
Nice to meet you, nugs.

06:01.980 --> 06:04.148
Nice meeting you too.

06:04.149 --> 06:06.116
Peace.

06:06.617 --> 06:09.220
There.
A hundred bucks.

06:09.221 --> 06:11.522
Oh, my God, Max,
that's a hundred-dollar bill!

06:11.523 --> 06:13.023
How easy was that?

06:13.024 --> 06:14.892
And we didn't even
have to open the shop.

06:14.893 --> 06:16.794
I mean, what is the problem
with doing this?

06:16.795 --> 06:18.529
You're right,
I overreacted.

06:18.530 --> 06:20.698
We're not selling pot.
We're selling cupcakes.

06:20.699 --> 06:21.932
We didn't break any laws.

06:21.933 --> 06:23.267
There's nothing illegal
about it.

06:23.268 --> 06:24.802
- Move! Move! Move!
- [Screams]

06:24.803 --> 06:25.803
I didn't know!
I didn't know!

06:25.804 --> 06:27.304
Go! Go! Go!
Keep going, now!

06:27.305 --> 06:29.807
- Police!
- Go! Go, now!

06:29.808 --> 06:33.141
Put the meth down!
Put the meth down!

06:35.280 --> 06:38.282
'Sup?

06:38.283 --> 06:40.184
Move! Go! Go!
Get him out! Let's go!

06:40.185 --> 06:42.186
Bring him out!
Go! Go! Go!

06:42.187 --> 06:44.555
I told you not to get involved
with drugs!

06:44.556 --> 06:45.656
I told you!

06:45.657 --> 06:48.726
- Shut it, Carol! Shut it!
- Oh!

06:53.131 --> 06:55.199
I can't believe
that just happened.

06:55.200 --> 06:58.533
I know, it's like,
"let it go, Carol."

06:59.237 --> 07:01.972
We're done with drugs.
I was right.

07:01.973 --> 07:05.042
And now you know
why my friends don't like you.

07:12.132 --> 07:13.798
And remember,
we do private parties,

07:13.799 --> 07:15.467
wedding parties,
birthday parties--

07:15.468 --> 07:18.169
All right, there's a dozen.
What's the special occasion?

07:18.170 --> 07:20.238
My cat died.

07:20.989 --> 07:23.572
We also do funerals,
divorces...

07:24.911 --> 07:27.345
And sad Friday nights alone.

07:27.346 --> 07:30.215
[Mouthing words]
Thank you.

07:30.216 --> 07:32.050
Okay, so that's
48 more dollars.

07:32.051 --> 07:35.384
Now, all we need is--
For 72 more cats to die.

07:35.721 --> 07:37.856
Max, there's no need
to kill imaginary cats.

07:37.857 --> 07:39.524
Let's just send out
positive energy,

07:39.525 --> 07:42.227
and the universe
will provide.

07:42.228 --> 07:45.530
Swing and a miss, universe.

07:45.531 --> 07:47.532
Surprise!
I was in the neighborhood

07:47.533 --> 07:49.167
and thought I'd stop by
and say hello.

07:49.168 --> 07:51.903
Under any other circumstance,
I'd say, "never do that again,"

07:51.904 --> 07:54.406
but today, I'm saying,
"how many cupcakes do you want""

07:54.407 --> 07:56.675
and I'm thinking of a number
between 10 and 20.

07:56.676 --> 07:59.144
I'm kind of trying
to watch my waist.

07:59.145 --> 08:02.247
Well, you're closer to it
than most people.

08:04.783 --> 08:06.685
I'm gonna start you
with 12 cupcakes.

08:06.686 --> 08:08.987
Full price,
'cause you're family.

08:08.988 --> 08:10.021
[Phone ringing]

08:10.022 --> 08:12.023
Oh, my God!
The phone ringing

08:12.024 --> 08:13.692
and a customer
at the same time?

08:13.693 --> 08:15.160
See, Max,
it's all happening.

08:15.161 --> 08:16.761
Between the money
we just got last night

08:16.762 --> 08:18.997
and that pregnant girl's
<i>Quinceanera</i> / Baby shower,

08:18.998 --> 08:20.498
we're gonna
make our rent.

08:20.499 --> 08:23.468
Max's Homemade Cupcakes.
Oh, <i>hola,</i> Estella.

08:23.469 --> 08:25.704
<i>Si,</i>
the <i>Quinceanera</i> / Baby shower.

08:25.995 --> 08:27.772
<i>Que?</i>

08:27.773 --> 08:31.106
Oh, no.
Deported?

08:31.243 --> 08:34.312
Oh, you can't afford it.
[Chuckles]

08:37.616 --> 08:39.618
My <i>mal.</i>

08:39.619 --> 08:42.952
Well, sorry, it didn't work out.
<i>Gracias</i> for calling.

08:43.121 --> 08:44.756
Well, that's disappointing,

08:44.757 --> 08:45.957
but we should have
seen it coming.

08:45.958 --> 08:49.291
She couldn't
afford condoms either.

08:49.862 --> 08:50.895
It's cool.

08:50.896 --> 08:52.130
I'll just call Keefer

08:52.131 --> 08:53.598
and try to do
a couple more cupcake runs.

08:53.599 --> 08:56.334
No, that's not cool,
that's dangerous.

08:56.335 --> 08:58.503
It'll all work out.
You know what?

08:58.504 --> 09:00.038
I'm just gonna go over
and ask Andy

09:00.039 --> 09:02.407
if he'll float us some cash
till the holiday rush kicks in.

09:02.408 --> 09:03.441
He did offer.

09:03.442 --> 09:05.477
We should put up
some Christmas lights,

09:05.478 --> 09:07.912
a menorah for Chanukah,
and for Kwanzaa...

09:08.213 --> 09:11.246
While I'm gone, why don't you
Wikipedia Kwanzaa?

09:13.284 --> 09:15.717
Well...
Here's the first eight.

09:16.188 --> 09:17.656
And how many cupcakes
would you like "to go"?

09:17.657 --> 09:20.025
I'm thinking of a number
between 40 and 50.

09:20.026 --> 09:23.161
How come you never push
the food at the diner like this?

09:23.162 --> 09:26.495
Oh, that's where
I know you from.

09:28.467 --> 09:30.535
Start eating.

09:36.875 --> 09:39.208
I didn't do it.
It's so not hot.

09:39.311 --> 09:40.578
He's my boyfriend.
I mean,

09:40.579 --> 09:42.347
it's not like borrowing money
from family.

09:42.348 --> 09:44.716
You don't sleep
with your family.

09:44.717 --> 09:48.050
Not all families
are the same, Caroline.

09:48.554 --> 09:51.387
Besides, we're fine.
The universe will provide.

09:51.390 --> 09:53.358
Well, the universe
better provide in,

09:53.359 --> 09:54.893
like, a second, 'cause look,
there's the landlord.

09:54.894 --> 09:56.828
He just went
into that Moroccan place.

09:56.829 --> 09:57.829
What are we
gonna do?

09:57.830 --> 09:58.963
- Hide!
- What?

09:58.964 --> 10:00.899
Well, I should go.

10:00.900 --> 10:02.400
It's too late for that!

10:02.401 --> 10:03.535
Lock the door, hit the lights,

10:03.536 --> 10:05.804
and crawl over here,
and stay low!

10:05.805 --> 10:08.073
Stay down
till we're out of sight.

10:08.074 --> 10:09.074
Ow!

10:09.075 --> 10:12.408
Ow. Ow, it hurts!

10:12.445 --> 10:14.379
Oh, please.
Like this is the first time

10:14.380 --> 10:16.815
you've been on your knees
in the bathroom.

10:16.816 --> 10:19.017
Caroline, you don't have to
stay on the ground anymore.

10:19.018 --> 10:21.586
I feel like
this is where I belong now.

10:22.587 --> 10:24.489
[Keys jangling]
Yo, Baker girls.

10:24.490 --> 10:25.824
Max, he's in the shop.

10:25.825 --> 10:27.992
- Okay, go, out the window.
- Really?

10:27.993 --> 10:29.728
If he can't see us,
he can't evict us.

10:29.729 --> 10:32.831
Go.

10:32.832 --> 10:35.467
It's a little high.
Are you sure?

10:35.468 --> 10:38.636
You've heard "When God closes
a door, he opens a window"?

10:38.637 --> 10:39.904
He's running
from his landlord.

10:39.905 --> 10:41.107
Go.

10:42.108 --> 10:44.976
Okay, here goes.
I love you, Max.

10:48.114 --> 10:49.748
What about me?
What should I do?

10:49.749 --> 10:52.517
Put the money for those
cupcakes on the counter.

10:57.089 --> 10:58.356
Who are you?

10:58.357 --> 10:59.640
Uh...

10:59.997 --> 11:01.690
<i>No hablo ingles?</i>

11:05.643 --> 11:06.976
All right, all right,
good news.

11:06.977 --> 11:09.612
I just found $3
in my pocket.

11:09.613 --> 11:11.281
Oh, and a peanut M&M,

11:11.282 --> 11:13.449
so we don't have to
spend money on dinner.

11:13.450 --> 11:15.451
Caroline,
why are you putting it off?

11:15.452 --> 11:16.853
You know
what you have to do.

11:16.854 --> 11:19.122
Go over to the couch and
put your hands in that crack.

11:19.123 --> 11:21.958
It's every poor girl's
rite of passage.

11:23.694 --> 11:24.961
Oh!

11:24.962 --> 11:25.962
What?

11:25.963 --> 11:28.232
I think something
just licked me.

11:29.993 --> 11:32.068
I'll just check our purses.
Here's yours.

11:32.069 --> 11:33.336
Uh, no, no, no.
I already checked that.

11:33.337 --> 11:34.470
There's nothing
in mine...

11:34.471 --> 11:36.005
Except that baggie of pot

11:36.006 --> 11:38.541
that Keefer gave me
as a Christmas present.

11:38.542 --> 11:40.343
Max, this is not
a Christmas present.

11:40.344 --> 11:43.112
This is a giant, illegal,
fat sack of weed.

11:43.113 --> 11:45.815
Yeah,
with a Rudolph sticker,

11:45.816 --> 11:47.750
which makes it
a Christmas present.

11:47.751 --> 11:50.653
See?
His nose and his eyes are red.

11:51.654 --> 11:53.987
I want this out of my sight.
You gotta get rid of it.

11:54.124 --> 11:55.692
[Scoffs]
Well, it's gonna take me

11:55.693 --> 11:58.227
at least 45 minutes
to smoke all that.

11:58.228 --> 11:59.729
Max, I'm serious,

11:59.730 --> 12:01.931
I'm not comfortable
with that fat sack of weed.

12:01.932 --> 12:04.601
Stop saying
"fat sack of weed."

12:04.602 --> 12:07.170
You're like someone's dad
overusing the word "awesome."

12:08.171 --> 12:09.672
I'll just
put it up here,

12:09.673 --> 12:13.006
next to the half a Vicodin
I was saving for new year's.

12:14.044 --> 12:15.044
[Screams]

12:15.045 --> 12:16.946
Oh, no!
The pot!

12:16.947 --> 12:18.314
The pot is in the pot!

12:18.315 --> 12:20.850
It's in the butter
I was using to make cupcakes.

12:20.851 --> 12:21.918
Maybe this is
the universe's way

12:21.919 --> 12:23.920
of telling you
to stop doing drugs.

12:23.921 --> 12:27.254
Or is it telling us
to sell them?

12:29.826 --> 12:32.328
Max, we are
not that desperate.

12:32.329 --> 12:33.763
We're not making
pot cupcakes.

12:33.764 --> 12:35.865
I'd rather just see
what the holidays bring.

12:35.866 --> 12:38.234
Well, this isn't Bethlehem,
it's Brooklyn.

12:38.235 --> 12:40.003
There's no frankincense
and myrrh,

12:40.004 --> 12:42.672
there's only frankenberry
and "myrrh-ajuana."

12:50.788 --> 12:53.221
These turned out great!
Good idea, universe.

12:53.422 --> 12:56.491
I knew you smoked weed.

12:56.492 --> 12:58.894
Oh, my God.
I can't believe the smell.

12:58.895 --> 13:02.063
It's like a skunk
skunked a skunk.

13:02.064 --> 13:04.232
